  "prompt": "What can I give my best friend on her birthday?",
  "response": "Choosing a gift for your best friend can be a fun and personal experience. Here are some thoughtful ideas to consider:\n\n1. **Personalized Jewelry**: A necklace or bracelet with her initials, a meaningful date, or a special message.\n\n2. **Custom Photo Album or Scrapbook**: Compile photos and memories of your friendship, with little notes or captions.\n\n3. **Experience Gifts**: Plan a day out together, such as a spa day, concert tickets, or a cooking class.\n\n4. **Subscription Box**: Choose a subscription that aligns with her interests, like beauty products, books, or snacks.\n\n5. **Handwritten Letters**: Write a series of letters that she can open on different occasions (e.g., when she\u2019s sad, happy, etc.).\n\n6. **Personalized Mug or Tumbler**: Design a mug with an inside joke or a photo of the two of you.\n\n7. **Cozy Gifts**: A soft blanket, scented candles, or a set of bath bombs for some self-care days.\n\n8. **Books**: If she loves reading, consider a book by her favorite author or a genre she enjoys.\n\n9. **DIY Kit**: A fun craft kit, cooking set, or anything she can make or create.\n\n10. **Gift Card**: If you\u2019re unsure of her exact preferences, a gift card to her favorite store or restaurant can be a great option.\n\nUltimately, consider her interests and what would mean the most to her. Personal touches always make a gift extra special!",
